  "2026-06-18T23:13:15.492Z",claude-code-agent,"Release-health verification 2026-06-19 (post PR#290 merge): (1) Last published = npm 2026.6.17 == git v2026.6.17 (aligned). (2) The 2026-06-18 07:17Z scheduled Auto Release FAILED on a git push non-fast-forward — but that run executed BEFORE the push-retry fix bf35af26 merged at 16:19 CEST, so it ran old code. The fetch+rebase+retry now lives in scripts/release/run-release-pipeline.mjs pushReleaseRefs. (3) Manually dispatched Auto Release dry-run on current main (run 27794655651): FULLY GREEN — build, docs/static/coverage gates, tests, version compute, changelog, and the Sentry reliability gate all pass. (4) Telemetry stack healthy: all containers up, API ok (v2026.6.17), RabbitMQ queue drained (0 ready), 15061 Postgres events/24h (real-time). (5) Sentry: queryable with admin token; newest unresolved issue 2026-06-13, all expected CommandErrors, NO new errors from PR#290. Conclusion: the next scheduled cron (35 2 * * * UTC) will publish 2026.6.18/.19 automatically with the fixed push path. Verify npm picks it up after the next run."
