  "2026-07-05T16:12:03.034Z",claude-code-agent,"Review fix evidence for PR #451: accepted CodeRabbit's spoofing finding and tightened the issues.closed retry path so production retries require the exact Auto Release blocked issue title and github-actions[bot] as the issue author. This prevents arbitrary public users from opening and closing a same-title issue to trigger the release environment. Focused validation rerun: workflow contract test and pinned actionlint."
  "2026-07-05T16:18:32.536Z",claude-code-agent,"Review follow-up evidence for PR #451: addressed hosted Greptile feedback after CodeRabbit's spoofing fix by enforcing the documented same-UTC-day retry window for issues.closed retries and by adding a closed-issue comment when a retry succeeds without publishing a new tag. Docs now match the workflow contract. Validation passed: node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/integration/ci-workflow-contract.spec.ts and pinned actionlint 1.7.12 against .github/workflows/auto-release.yml."
  "2026-07-05T16:22:10.266Z",claude-code-agent,"Greptile follow-up evidence for PR #451: local Greptile review 8799a161-0bc3-4430-b260-0f4e5d4d3d46 found the retry-failure issue comment still said the scheduled daily run failed. Fixed the alert body and detected-cause text to branch between scheduled runs and blocker-resolution retries, with workflow contract coverage for both messages. Validation passed after the fix: focused ci-workflow-contract test, pinned actionlint 1.7.12, pnpm lint, and git diff --check."
  "2026-07-05T16:25:16.309Z",claude-code-agent,"Greptile edge-case evidence for PR #451: addressed hosted Greptile's cleanup-closure retrigger concern by requiring github.actor != github-actions[bot] for issues.closed retry execution and retry success/skip/failure steps. This keeps workflow-created scheduled-success cleanup from launching another production retry. Docs now define one retry attempt per same-day maintainer/agent closure, and failed retries still reopen the blocker for a later closure after additional remediation. Validation passed: focused ci-workflow-contract test, pinned actionlint 1.7.12, pnpm lint, and git diff --check."
  "2026-07-05T16:29:06.253Z",claude-code-agent,"Greptile contract evidence for PR #451: local Greptile review 4099afe0-fafc-4000-8b64-4ad609351752 found the issues.closed trigger itself was not pinned by the auto-release workflow contract test. Added explicit auto-release assertions for issues:, types:, and - closed. Validation passed after the correction: focused ci-workflow-contract test, pnpm lint, and git diff --check."
  "2026-07-05T16:40:56.916Z",claude-code-agent,"Greptile multi-day evidence for PR #451: addressed local Greptile review a6f06522-afed-4615-ae53-55d76e7e8064 by rolling stale prior-day open Auto Release blockers into a fresh current-day bot-created blocker on the next scheduled failure. This keeps same-day retry detection tied to the latest scheduled failure while the github-actions actor guard prevents workflow cleanup closures from retriggering Auto Release. Validation passed: focused ci-workflow-contract test, pinned actionlint 1.7.12, pnpm lint, and git diff --check."
  "2026-07-05T16:44:00.393Z",claude-code-agent,"CodeRabbit follow-up evidence for PR #451: accepted the actionable retry-notification feedback by making resolved-issue retry success/skip comments non-fatal when gh issue comment fails, preventing a GitHub API comment outage from converting a successful retry into the failure alert/reopen path. Also simplified retry outcome step conditions to rely on the pinned job-level issue guard. Validation passed: focused ci-workflow-contract test, pinned actionlint 1.7.12, pnpm lint, and git diff --check."
  "2026-07-05T16:47:36.115Z",claude-code-agent,"Greptile cosmetic evidence for PR #451: accepted local Greptile review e3265bff-c5b8-4b6c-b0f9-b8df03da08a6 by switching stale-blocker superseded_body construction to printf -v so Run/Commit metadata renders as plain Markdown instead of an indented code block. Added contract coverage for the printf body builder. Validation passed: focused ci-workflow-contract test, pinned actionlint 1.7.12, pnpm lint, and git diff --check."
  "2026-07-05T16:56:26.498Z",claude-code-agent,"Greptile documentation evidence for PR #451: accepted local Greptile review 0edf8de2-599c-4723-952c-0f4a51d8e177 doc feedback by documenting the successful-publish retry outcome comment alongside skip-comment and reopen-on-failure behavior. Validation passed: pnpm quality:docs-links and git diff --check."
  "2026-07-05T17:04:18.812Z",claude-code-agent,"Greptile failure-path evidence for PR #451: accepted local Greptile review cc7c4ec7-6835-46fa-a05e-5ed5bafd8122 by guarding the retry-failure gh issue comment and gh issue reopen independently. A comment API failure now logs and continues to the reopen attempt, so failed retries do not leave the blocker closed silently. Validation passed: focused ci-workflow-contract test, pinned actionlint 1.7.12, pnpm lint, and git diff --check."
  "2026-07-05T17:22:21.939Z",codex,"Review-loop evidence: Hosted Greptile flagged duplicate same-day blocker retries after a failed resolved-issue Auto Release retry. Added a current-day retry marker on the blocker issue before running the production retry, refuse duplicate same-day attempts before release mutation, documented the behavior in docs/RELEASING.md, and pinned the marker/issue-number contract in tests/integration/ci-workflow-contract.spec.ts. Validation: node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/integration/ci-workflow-contract.spec.ts; pinned actionlint 1.7.12 on .github/workflows/auto-release.yml; pnpm lint; pnpm quality:docs-links; pm health --check-only --summary --json; pm validate --check-resolution --check-history-drift --json (known validate_resolution_missing_fields:268, history drift ok); git diff --check."
  "2026-07-05T17:33:17.660Z",codex,"Review-loop evidence: accepted CodeRabbit finding on PR #451 that an untrusted issue comment could spoof the same-day retry marker. Hardened auto-release.yml so duplicate retry detection only reads marker comments authored by github-actions[bot], and pinned that jq author filter in ci-workflow-contract.spec.ts. Validation rerun: node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/integration/ci-workflow-contract.spec.ts; pinned actionlint 1.7.12 on .github/workflows/auto-release.yml; pnpm lint; git diff --check."
  "2026-07-05T17:35:17.896Z",codex,"Review-loop evidence: accepted local Greptile finding that retry marker refusal paths should not exit as failures because that would reopen the blocker and invite another close. Updated auto-release.yml so missing issue number, unreadable retry state, and duplicate current-day marker each emit explicit retry_skip_reason outputs and exit 0 through the resolved-issue skip comment path. Docs now describe safely refused retries, and ci-workflow-contract pins retry_issue_number_unavailable, retry_state_unavailable, and retry_already_attempted. Validation rerun: focused ci-workflow-contract test, pinned actionlint 1.7.12, pnpm lint, pnpm quality:docs-links, git diff --check."
  "2026-07-05T17:47:17.275Z",codex,"Review-loop evidence: accepted Gemini Code Assist finding on PR #451 that deleted-user comments can return null authors. Updated the retry-marker comment scan to use .author?.login in the gh --jq filter, keeping marker trust restricted to github-actions[bot] while tolerating null authors, and pinned the exact filter in ci-workflow-contract.spec.ts. Validation rerun: focused ci-workflow-contract test, pinned actionlint 1.7.12, pnpm lint, git diff --check."
  "2026-07-05T18:00:40.704Z",codex,"Review-loop evidence: accepted Gemini Code Assist correction that gh --jq uses jq optional suffix syntax, not JavaScript optional chaining. Replaced .author?.login with .author.login? in the trusted retry-marker comment filter, added a jq syntax check over null-author data, and kept the contract assertion in sync. Validation rerun: jq -n null-author filter check, focused ci-workflow-contract test, pinned actionlint 1.7.12, pnpm lint, git diff --check."
  "2026-07-06T13:13:56.740Z",maintainer-agent,"Release-health check 2026-07-06 (audit #10): auto-release cut 2026.7.6 (commit 02b91bac) and npm shows @unbrained/pm-cli latest publishes 2026.7.4 / 2026.7.5 / 2026.7.6 — three consecutive daily releases published. Auto-release pipeline confirmed healthy."
  "2026-07-07T14:29:16.140Z",maintainer-agent,"Release-health check 2026-07-07 (planning pass #27): npm shows @unbrained/pm-cli latest 2026.7.7; GitHub release v2026.7.7 cut 06:48Z. Four consecutive daily releases (2026.7.4-2026.7.7) published. Auto-release pipeline confirmed healthy."
  "2026-07-07T15:26:16.229Z",maintainer-agent,"2026-07-07 release-health verification (planning pass, later same day): npm @unbrained/pm-cli latest is 2026.7.7 (published today), local package.json matches, CHANGELOG [Unreleased] is empty, and the 15:09Z Auto Release run correctly skipped on the empty section. CI at HEAD (c4df9945): Security and Script Quality passed; CI + CodeQL in progress at check time with no failures. Healthy — daily cut landed and the post-cut skip behaved as designed."
  "2026-07-07T15:58:16.538Z",maintainer-agent,"Release-health verification 2026-07-07 (planning pass): npm dist-tag latest for @unbrained/pm-cli = 2026.7.7, matching package.json — today's daily cut published successfully (commit 969cb352 \"chore(release): cut 2026.7.7\"). Post-cut auto-release runs report \"skipped\" (empty [Unreleased]) which is the healthy steady state. CI, CodeQL, and Security/Script Quality all green on the latest main pushes. Validate warning drift unchanged at 147 missing-linked-paths / 125 orphaned-paths / 269 resolution-missing-fields / 18 missing-close-reason; the single duplicate-issue-code warning (GH-209 pair pm-1byt/pm-25se) remains owned by pm-pivf pending the pm-m4iu -> pm-wrbe closed_at chain."
  "2026-07-07T20:26:56.420Z",maintainer-agent,"Release-health evidence 2026-07-07 (evening pass): npm @unbrained/pm-cli serves 2026.7.7 — today's date-based cut is live. The three auto-release runs after the cut all concluded skipped (empty [Unreleased] guard), the healthy post-cut signature. Validate warning drift unchanged at 147 missing-linked-paths / 125 orphaned-paths / 269 resolution-missing-fields / 18 missing-close-reason plus the single pm-pivf-owned duplicate issue-code — steady state, no new comment-worthy movement."
  "2026-07-08T04:51:09.535Z",maintainer-agent,"Release-health verification 2026-07-08 (planning pass): npm @unbrained/pm-cli latest = 2026.7.7, matching the 2026-07-07 cut; [Unreleased] holds three entries (pm-6abs, pm-alnj, pm-kffw) awaiting today's scheduled daily cut — healthy pending state. Issue-triggered auto-release runs on 07-07 correctly skipped. CI on main green; PR #481 (SDK context primitives lane) open with all checks green, its pm items (pm-usfg/pm-w89s/pm-x6jf/pm-cbwg) correctly in_progress."
  "2026-07-10T10:35:41.956Z",maintainer-agent,"Release health 2026-07-10: auto-release cut 2026.7.10 cleanly (abb1a524) after PR #493 fixed the Sentry gate misclassifying handled duplicate-import dogfood errors (pm-io4t/pm-yohx closed). Validate drift CHANGE since 2026-07-09: files orphaned 125->124 (improved), resolution_missing 269->272 (+3 from new closes without the structured triple — faucet now tracked as pm-wenq, legacy mop stays pm-e9zh). Steady: linked_paths 147, close_reason 18 (pre-enforcement, pm-e9zh), GH-209 dup pair 1 (pm-pivf, both closed). All checks green otherwise; history drift ok."
  "2026-07-10T10:47:36.349Z",maintainer-agent,"Release health 2026-07-10: scheduled auto-release run FAILED this morning (Sentry reliability gate misclassified handled duplicate-import dogfood errors as blocking). Fixed same day by PR #493 (pm-io4t narrow expected-handled classifier; pm-yohx count-agnostic brittle patterns), release 2026.7.10 cut (commit abb1a524) and verified live on npm (@unbrained/pm-cli 2026.7.10). No maintainer action needed; faucet class now has two shipped hardening fixes."
  "2026-07-10T12:16:32.745Z",maintainer-agent,"2026-07-10: auto-release RECOVERED — v2026.7.10 cut 09:34Z and live on npm. The 2026-07-09 scheduled-run failure was the Sentry reliability gate misclassifying handled duplicate-import dogfood errors as blocking (pm-io4t, pm-yohx — both closed via PR#493). Post-cut 11:37Z run skipped = healthy."
  "2026-07-10T16:22:34.716Z",maintainer-agent,"2026-07-10 (later pass): first fully-clean cycle post-recovery. v2026.7.10 live; PR #499 merged 16:06Z with all gates green (Docs/Security/CodeQL success, Auto Release correctly skipped post-cut); [Unreleased] repopulated by the five schema-fidelity closures, awaiting the 2026.7.11 daily cut. No pipeline action needed."
  "2026-07-12T06:09:46.899Z",maintainer-agent,"2026-07-12 scheduled Auto Release run 29181568390 FAILED (first failure since RELEASE_PAT fix): sentry-telemetry-gate blocked on PM-CLI-26 + PM-CLI-10 — both torn-install bundle transients from the operator host (stale hashed chunk generation; verified non-reproducible), NOT 2026.7.11 regressions. Both resolved in Sentry after live verification; Auto Release re-triggered same day. Class fix owned by pm-wfvq (boot-time bundle-integrity self-check + distinct gate-classifiable error code). GH-521 = the auto-filed ops alert, pm-linked to pm-wfvq."
  "2026-07-12T06:56:56.581Z",maintainer-agent,"Recovery confirmed 2026-07-12: v2026.7.12 published to npm + GitHub (publish run 29182944895 success) after same-day re-trigger; GH-521 closed. Operational trap recorded: manual 'gh workflow run Auto Release' defaults push=false — the pipeline runs green, cuts the version in the runner, and publishes NOTHING; recovery dispatches must pass -f push=true."
  "2026-07-12T08:08:33.503Z",maintainer-agent,"2026-07-12: PM-CLI-27 (AbortError: Ctrl+C, error-level) triaged as user-initiated interrupt and resolved in Sentry so it cannot block the next auto-release gate run; class fix (capture-time classification of deliberate aborts) = pm-ksv2. Per pm-wfvq rule, NOT added to the gate's environment patterns."
  "2026-07-12T13:35:10.902Z",maintainer-agent,"Release-health evidence 2026-07-12: scheduled Auto Release run 29181568390 failed, then workflow_dispatch runs 29182238706 and 29182573202 succeeded; GitHub release v2026.7.12 and npm @unbrained/pm-cli 2026.7.12 are both live. No release duplicate created."
  "2026-07-13T19:42:42.768Z",codex-root,"Live release-health evidence 2026-07-13: latest Auto Release run 29269678835 completed successfully in 38s on main via workflow_dispatch; subsequent issue-triggered runs show the expected skipped steady state. This context branch does not change release workflow code. Local release gates remain blocked only by the two already-canonical live Sentry classes pm-wfvq/PM-CLI-26 and pm-ksv2/PM-CLI-27; no duplicate release item created."
  "2026-07-14T10:18:55.943Z",codex-gpt5,"Live release-health evidence 2026-07-14: scheduled Auto Release run 29308023886 succeeded on 4d5d405b; GitHub release v2026.7.14 published at 05:27Z and npm latest is 2026.7.14. The automatic daily pipeline is currently healthy. This SDK branch does not alter release automation; live Sentry PM-CLI-29 remains separately tracked by pm-7n5a."
  "2026-07-15T06:21:11.875Z",maintainer-agent,"Release-health change 2026-07-15: scheduled Auto Release run 29390986598 FAILED at the aggregate release gate — Sentry check threshold_ok:false with 2 blocking highs PM-CLI-2B (pm-d4ns) and PM-CLI-29 (pm-7n5a), both P1 under pm-5oj5. No v2026.7.15 release cut yet; RELEASE_PAT and tokens configured (preflight healthy); GH-566 auto-filed. Recovery path is fixing/classifying d4ns+7n5a, then re-run Auto Release with -f push=true."
  "2026-07-15T18:17:36.278Z",codex-root,"Recovery start 2026-07-15: merged SDK PR #568 is on main at ec3f0ee9. Live scheduled Auto Release run 29390986598 failed only because PM-CLI-2B and PM-CLI-29 were unresolved at 05:21Z. Full live reads confirm canonical owner fixes pm-d4ns and pm-7n5a are now closed with published pm-changelog@2026.7.15-1 and pm-graph@2026.7.15, both Sentry groups are resolved with no recurrence, and the current Sentry gate reports zero highs. GH-566 is the same-day blocker issue whose close event is designed to trigger one production retry; proceeding with that recovery path rather than creating duplicate work."
  "2026-07-15T18:32:03.081Z",codex-root,"Recovery completion 2026-07-15: GH-566 close triggered guarded same-day Auto Release run 29439966148 on merged SDK head ec3f0ee9; it completed successfully in 12m24s and waited for tag-push Release run 29440310562, which also succeeded. GitHub release v2026.7.15 is latest, npm @unbrained/pm-cli latest is 2026.7.15, and the release commit is 27ca89ed. Live post-release reliability proof: Sentry release pm-cli@2026.7.15 is registered; 14-day gate reports critical=0, high=0, access_ok=true; telemetry is real-time and healthy at 0.33 percent finish error rate with zero failures missing error_code. PR #568 merged as ec3f0ee9, project health is ok, history drift is zero, and pm-changelog 2026.7.15-1 reports CHANGELOG.md current. Returning this recurring reminder to open after successful verification."
  "2026-07-16T05:41:27.715Z",maintainer-agent,"Release health 2026-07-16: auto-release run 29473844016 SUCCESS; v2026.7.16 live on GitHub Releases (05:38Z) and npm latest. First routine fully-unblocked daily cut after the 2026-07-15 Sentry-gate recovery (PR#568/#570). No intervention needed."
  "2026-07-16T21:18:37.715Z",codex-wide-sdk-20260716,"2026-07-16 release-health evidence: scheduled Auto Release run 29473844016 succeeded and v2026.7.16 is live. Current authenticated Sentry query reports critical=0/high=0, 17 expected handled CommandError groups, and telemetry is real-time at 0.33% finish-error rate with zero failures missing error_code. Local linked release-gate sandbox omitted Sentry credentials by design; injecting the existing read token made the strict gate pass."
  "2026-07-17T13:31:53.750Z",codex-root,"Release-health evidence 2026-07-17: scheduled Auto Release run 29571834562 succeeded; GitHub release v2026.7.17 published at 05:38Z and npm @unbrained/pm-cli latest is 2026.7.17. The automatic daily release path is currently healthy. npm pm-changelog latest is 2026.7.15-1 and will be reinstalled for this branch's package-owned changelog generation after final tracker mutations."
