docs[1]{path,scope,note}:
  docs/RELEASING.md,project,document scheduled publish closing blocked auto-release issues
body: "## Procedure (run after any merge to main)\n1. Next day (or after the daily workflow window), check: `gh run list --workflow=auto-release` → latest run green.\n2. Confirm a new tag vYYYY.M.D exists AND `npm view @unbrained/pm-cli version` advanced to match (both must hold — tagging without publish has happened).\n3. If either failed: inspect the run log; known past failure modes are (a) padded-vs-unpadded month in the changelog-match step silently skipping the release (fixed 2026-05-28), (b) publish/Sentry-gate step failing post-tag (needs SENTRY auth token in release env), (c) missing issues:write permission (fixed PR#364). RELEASE_PAT is configured — auto-release is currently healthy (2026-07-04: v2026.7.4 cut).\n\n## Why a Reminder item\nThe release train fails SILENTLY (empty [Unreleased] or a skipped match just means \"no release\"), so a standing recurring check is the only reliable detection. Keep this item OPEN permanently; log each verification as a note/comment here instead of closing."
